Description: Fragment of oval handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay near fine pink-buff.
Curator's comments: Name Aristonidas. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.136, 2. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 412.08.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0688)
